HTML Tag Dictionary


# 


	<!---->
	Function:
		defines a comment
		The comment is not shown in the website.
	Encoding Formula:	
	<!--(Comments)-->


	<!DOCTYPE>
	Function:
		defines the document type.
		very first thing in your HTML document, before the <html> tag.
		<!DOCTYPE> declaration is not an HTML tag.
		It is an instruction to the web browser about what version of HTML the page is written in.
	Encoding Formula:
		<!DOCTYPE>


A


	<a>
	Function:
		defines a hyperlink
		used to link from one page to another
	Attributes:
		href attribute is used to indicate the link's destination.
	Encoding Formula: </h4>
		<a href="(Website URL)">(Click button)</a>


B


	<b>
	Function:
		defines bold text
		specifies bold text without any extra importance
	Encoding Formula:
		<b>(Bolded Contents)</b>


	<body>
	Function:
		defines the document's body.
		contains the cotents of the webpage such as text, hyperlinks, images, tables, lists, etc.
	Encoding Formula:
		<body>(Contents)</body>


	<br>
	Functions:
		inserts single line break
		is a empty tag: no end tag
	Encoding Formula:
		Line #1<br>Line #2
		
		
C


D
	<div>
	Function:
		defines a division or a section in an HTML document.
		often used as a container for other HTML elements to style them with CSS
	Encoding Formula:
		<div>Divided Contents</div>

E


F


G


H


	<h1~6>
	Function:
		defines HTML heading
		<h1> defines the most important heading. <h6> defines the least important heading.
	Attribute:
		align attribute specifies the alignment of a heading.
			"center" value center-aligns the heading.
			"left" value left-aligns the heading. 
			"right" value right-aligns the heading.
			"justify" value makes the heading is justified to both margins.
	Encoding Formula:
		<h1>Heading #1</h1>
		<h2>Heading #2</h2>
		<h3>Heading #3</h3>
		<h4>Heading #4</h4>
		<h5>Heading #5</h5>
		<h6>Heading #6</h6>


	<head>
	Function:
		defines information about the document
		can include a title for the document, scripts, styles, meta information, and more.
		The following tags can go inside the <head> tag:
			<title>
			<style>
			<base>
			<link>
			<meta>
			<script>
			<noscript>
		The <head> tag must be written above the <body> tag.
	Encoding Formula:
		<head>(Contents)</head>


	<html>
	Function:
		defines the root of an HTML document
		tells browsers where tthe HTML code starts and ends.
		The <html> tag is the container for all other HTML elements (except for the <!DOCTYPE> tag).
	Encoding Formula:
		<html>(Codes)</html>


I


	<img>
	Function:
		defines an image
	Attributes:
		src attribute specifies the URL for an image.
		alt attribute specifies an alternative text for an image, when the image cannot be displayed.
		height attribute specifies the height of the image.
		width attribute specifies the width of the image.
		*The image would be inserted by its actual size if height attribute and width attribute are not defined.
	Encoding Formula:
		<img src="(Image Name.[Image Type])" alt="(Image Name.[Image Type])" height="(Specific Image Height in Pixels)" width="(Specific Image Width in Pixels)">


J


K


L


	<li>
	Function:
		defines a list item used in ordered lists(<ol>), unordered lists (<ul>), and in menu lists (<menu>).
	Encoding Formula:
		<ol>Start of the Ordered List
			<li>Item #1</li>
			<li>Item #2</li>
			<li>Item #3</li>
		End of the Ordered List </ol>
		<ul>Start of the Unordered List
			<li>Item #1</li>
			<li>Item #2</li>
			<li>Item #3</li>
		End of the Unordered List </ul>


M


N


O


	<ol>
	Function:
		defines an ordered list
		An ordered list can be numerical or alphabetical.
		uses the <li> tag to list items.
	Attributes:
		reversed attribute is used to specify descending order.
			Ex. 9,8,7,6,5...
		start attribute can be used to specify the start value of an ordered list.
		type attribute can be used to specify the kind of marker to use in the list.
			"1" value specifies decimal numbers 
				Ex. 1, 2, 3, 4
				It is Default
			"a" value specidies alphabetically ordered list in lowercase.
				Ex. a, b, c, d
			"A" value specidies alphabetically ordered list in upercase.
				Ex. A, B, C, D
			"i" value specifies Roman numbers in lowercase.
				Ex. i, ii, iii, iv
			"I"	value specifies Roman numbers in uppercase.
				Ex. I, II, III, IV
	Encoding Formula:
		<ol> Start of the Ordered List
			<li>Item #1</li>
			<li>Item #2</li>
			<li>Item #3</li>
		</ol> End of the Ordered List

P


	<p>
	Function:
		defines a paragraph
		adds some space (margin) before and after each element.
	Encoding Formula:
		<p>Paragraph #1</p>
		<p>Paragraph #2</p>


Q



R



S


	<style>
	Function:
		defines style information for a document.
		placed in the <head> tag.
		used to specify how HTML elements should render in a browser.
			CSS informations are written here.
	Encoding Formula:
		<head>
		<style>
		(Tag Name) {
			(Attribute Name): (Value);
		{
		</style>
		</head>


T

	<table>
	Function:
		defines an HTML table
		consists of one or more <tr>, <th>, and <td> elements.
	Attributes:
		align attribute can be used to specify the alignment of a table according to surrounding text.
		bgcolor attribute can be used to specify the background color for a table.
		border attribute can be used to specify whether or not the table is being used for layout purposes.
		width attribute can be used to specify the width of a table.
	Encoding Formula:
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>Column Heading #1</th>
				<th>Column Heading #2</th>
				<th>Column Heading #3</th>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-1</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-2</td>
			</tr>
		</table>


	<td>
	Functions:
		defines a standard cell in an HTML table that contains data.
		regular and left-aligned by default
	Attributes:
		align attribute can be used to specify the alignment the content in the cell.
		bgcolor attribute can be used to specify the background color of a cell.
		height attribute can be used to specify the height of a cell.
		width attribute can be used to specify the width of a cell.
	Encoding Formula:
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>Column Heading #1</th>
				<th>Column Heading #2</th>
				<th>Column Heading #3</th>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-1</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-2</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		
		
	<th>
	Function:
		defines a header cell in an HTML table that contains header information.
		bold and centered by default
	Attributes:
		align attribute can be used to specify the alignment the content in the header cell.
		bgcolor attribute can be used to specify the background color of a header cell.
		height attribute can be used to specify the height of a header cell.
		width attribute can be used to specify the width of a header cell.
	Encoding Formula:
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>Column Heading #1</th>
				<th>Column Heading #2</th>
				<th>Column Heading #3</th>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-1</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-1</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td>Data in Cell 1-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 2-2</td>
				<td>Data in Cell 3-2</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		
		
U


V


	<video>
	Function:
		defines a video, movie, or other video streams
		supports only ".mp4", ".ogg", ".webm" file types.
		The videos which are directly brought from the Internet are only supported byChrome, Internet Explorer(Edge), FireFox, Safari, and Opera browsers.
			not supported in Internet Explorer 8 and earlier versions, versions belowOpera 25, and any other browsers.
		Embed files of online videos are copied here
	Attributes:
		src attribute is required for specifing the URL of the video file.
		height atribute can be used to set the height of the video player.
		width attribute can be used to set the width of the video player.
	Encoding Formula:
		<video src="(Video Name).(Video Type)"></video>


